t; reply with the concrete change; resolve thread.\n  - **Reject** when technically wrong; reply with evidence and leave for reviewer/Leo.\n  - **Postpone** when valid but out of scope; create/link an issue, reply with rationale.\n- Do not merge. Leo merges.\n\n## PR 1: Message History API\n\n**Branch:** `feat/chat-history-read-api`  \n**Base:** `main`  \n**Issues:** advances #77; references #53, #55, #86.\n\nChanges:\n- Add `GET /api/v1/chats/:id/messages`.\n- Add explicit DTOs: `ChatMessageResponse`, `ChatMessagesResponse`.\n- Use `TenantDbService.runAs`; missing/non-owned chat returns `404`.\n- Preserve ordered `UIMessage.parts`; reject non-text submitted parts remains enforced.\n- Add web fetch/query helpers only if they are testable without wiring UI yet.\n\nVerification:\n- `pnpm --filter api test`\n- `pnpm --filter api build`\n- `apps/api/scripts/rls-test.sh` if RLS/history authorization changes are touched.\n- `pnpm --filter web test` if web query helpers are added.\n\n## PR 2: Deep-Link Hydration\n\n**Branch:** `feat/chat-deeplink-hydration`  \n**Base:** `feat/chat-history-read-api`  \n**Issues:** closes #77 if complete; references #80, #86.\n\nChanges:\n- Add `/chat/[id]` route.\n- Extract current chat session logic from `page.tsx` into a reusable component/hook.\n- Hydrate `useChat` from `GET /api/v1/chats/:id/messages`.\n- Keep existing promptkit-style UI for this PR.\n- On new chat finish, adopt id and navigate/replace to `/chat/${chatId}` only after the server-side chat exists.\n- Update sidebar links/active state for routed chats.\n\nVerification:\n- `pnpm --filter web test`\n- `pnpm --filter web typecheck`\n- `pnpm --filter web lint`\n- `pnpm --filter web build`\n- `pnpm --filter api test`\n\n## PR 3: Add AI Elements Source\n\n**Branch:** `chore/add-ai-elements-components`  \n**Base:** `feat/chat-deeplink-hydration`  \n**Issues:** references new AI Elements tracking issue.\n\nChanges:\n- Run:\n  `pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add @ai-elements/conversation @ai-elements/message @ai-elements/prompt-input @ai-elements/reasoning -c apps/web`\n- Keep behavior unchanged; do not switch chat UI yet.\n- Commit generated AI Elements files separately from any manual fixes.\n- Patch generated source only for repo-required import paths and shadcn/design violations.\n- Keep attachment/file/screenshot affordances unavailable for now.\n\nVerification:\n- `pnpm --filter web typecheck`\n- `pnpm --filter web lint`\n- `pnpm --filter web build`\n- `pnpm build`\n\n## PR 4: Switch Chat UI To AI Elements\n\n**Branch:** `feat/chat-ai-elements-ui`  \n**Base:** `chore/add-ai-elements-components`  \n**Issues:** closes new AI Elements tracking issue; references #80 but does not close it unless full browser E2E is added.\n\nChanges:\n- Replace old local promptkit-style chat rendering with AI Elements:\n  - `Conversation`\n  - `ConversationContent`\n  - `ConversationScrollButton`\n  - `Message`\n  - `MessageContent`\n  - `MessageResponse`\n  - `Reasoning`\n  - `PromptInput`\n  - `PromptInputTextarea`\n  - `PromptInputSubmit`\n- Keep `DefaultChatTransport`, `authAwareFetch`, and `prepareSendMessagesRequest`.\n- Keep text-only UX. Hide or remove attachment controls.\n- Delete unused old local components after imports are gone:\n  - `apps/web/components/components/ai/chat-container.tsx`\n  - `apps/web/components/components/ai/message/*`\n  - `apps/web/components/components/ai/prompt-input.tsx`\n- Add a narrow route-intercepted Playwright/UI smoke if full #80 remains blocked by #50/test-provider work.\n- Leave #80 open unless the test covers real create → stream → render → switch chats against a server-runnable fake/stub model.\n\nVerification:\n- `pnpm --filter web test`\n- `pnpm --filter web typecheck`\n- `pnpm --filter web lint`\n- `pnpm --filter web build`\n- `pnpm build`\n- `pnpm test:e2e -- e2e/auth`\n- Run a local web preview and capture desktop/mobile screenshots for visual review.\n\n## Follow-Up Handling\n\n- If reviewers ask for full chat-flow E2E, either:\n  - implement it only if a server-runnable fake/stub model is in scope, or\n  - postpone into #80 with a concrete comment explaining that #80 remains blocked by #50/test-provider scope.\n- If reviewers ask for attachments/files, reject for this stack and create/link a future issue. Open WebUI-style file support requires ownership and authorization, not just UI controls.\n- If reviewers ask for assistant-ui, reject for this stack unless they identify a concrete AI Elements/runtime limitation. Create a comparison issue instead of mixing it into the migration.\n- If reviewers ask for durable stream replay, point to #49/#48/#50. Do not add run-event semantics to this UI migration.\n\n## Assumptions\n\n- Default branch is `main`.\n- The stack is intentionally linear; no parallel implementation PRs.\n- Each branch includes previous branch commits until prior PRs merge.\n- Changelog entries are added in the PR that ships the behavior.\n- No PR is merged by the agent.\n</proposed_plan>",
