          "text": "First, let's create a VISION.md document, akin to OpenClaw one.\n\nHere are my original ideas, used to write a SPEC.md:\n\n1) Multi-user from the ground-up: suitable for organizations, families, etc., allow admin group users together, configure MCPs, integrations, RAGs, etc., per-group, while still having global configuration, allow user configure connectors per-user, per-chat, per-project, etc. 2) integrated search RAG search for the chat history, chats have summaries, indexed for vectorized search if needed, multi-stage search by chat title, messages content, vectorized representation, summary, etc. 3) Concept of \"projects\" - can be shared with other people, etc. Projects may have their own connectors (MCPs, etc.), as well as \"artifacts\" storage for documents (markdown, word, etc.), ideally also vectorized for better search / RAG 4) Personal wiki-centric: for example, I have my own Obsidian, would be nice to have the personal wiki as the basis for everything, though this may be Obsidian for some, for others this might be a Notion, so this needs to be researched and even possibly made as an abstraction 5) Self-hosted using docker-compose, without any pain, safe, versionized, easy to deploy and microservice ready. Each message is processed by a worker, not the main thread, such that the page refresh restores current visible progress for the user 6) Interactive artifacts, aka Claude-style artifacts, but on the steroids, associated with GitHub repository, that may be ran and shared with others, may be even in the cloud / local sandbox if configured 7) BYOK for models / OAuth for providers, to allow users to connect their own LLM providers, such that even the full instance-level provider might not be configured 8) Interfaces for third-party messaging channels, OpenClaw-style, e.g., Telegram, Discord, etc.\n\nAdditionally, here are more things I envision now:\n1) \"Assistant\" personas, similar to subagent types here you have, and OpenClaw have, basically an initial prompt + persona + personal agent knowledge\n2) Option to connect existing machine as a connector to the Agent, to run actions on the user's machine when authorized, e.g., Claude Cowork, Claude Dispatch\n3) \"Brain\" concept from the Pewdipie's Odysseus agent\n4) Integration with email and calendar, to not only give a model access to users calendar events and mail, but display it in the interface, to be make an agent all-in-one toolkit\n5) n8n-like (or integration with it) to allow for workflows in the app, that can be both triggered by the assistant, by the user or by an automation (e.g., process mails, messages, etc.) with integration with the systems in the app, like knowledge base, tools, assistants, brains, memory, agents and so on",
