sion) — legacy JSON `access_control` blob still convertible |\n| hermes-agent | N/A — no group model; `user_id_alt` is same-platform alt ID, not cross-channel identity | N/A | N/A | `scope_id`/guild_id drives chat-level isolation only |\n| opencode | `workspace` = per-checkout scope tied to `project` (core); separate MySQL `workspace` = billing tenant (console/SaaS layer only) | N/A (not group nesting) | N/A in core; presumably in console (not inspected) | Not found in core/server |\n\nNone of the three gives llame a ready-made nested-group (org→team→project) model with per-membership roles — that part of SPEC.md's design has no direct precedent in these checkouts and will need original design, most likely closest in spirit to open-webui's `group`/`group_member` + normalized grants pattern, extended with a `parent_group_id` for nesting and a per-membership `role` column (which open-webui also lacks).</result>\n<usage><subagent_tokens>202028</subagent_tokens><tool_uses>5</tool_uses><duration_ms>97098</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>",
