oses when #45 lands (the issue's third\n  design step) — resolver and snapshot shapes already accommodate it.\n\nAlso in this change:\n- rls-test.sh now runs ALL *.integration suites serially — the pg-boss\n  queue suite owns real timing and must not contend with siblings\n  (parallel contention broke it nondeterministically).\n- worker-mode e2e stale window widened 2s → 30s: hand-staled zombies\n  (60s) still expire deterministically, but a CPU-starved LIVE run can\n  no longer be expired by the deadman mid-test (observed flake).\n- merge engine dodges a jest-VM realm pitfall: `constructor === Object`\n  is false for structuredClone output under jest — the check uses\n  realm-independent Object.prototype.toString.\n\nVerified on the isolated throwaway-Postgres harness (rls-test.sh):\n35/35 integration (7 new merge, 5 new configs-RLS) + 37 e2e incl. two\nnew tests — instance-layer budget provenance, and a user-scope config\noverriding env with provenance on the run row, the provider cap, and\nthe explain endpoint. 145 unit tests, lint, tsc, build green.\nFull-fleet e2e against the SHARED dev database is no longer meaningful\nevidence: any co-resident API process (e.g. a dev server, worker mode\nby default) legally consumes queued runs with real credentials — the\nexact shared-queue property #50 flagged; use rls-test.sh or Playwright\n(both throwaway-DB) for verification.\n\nRefs #46 — the deny-stripping acceptance step arrives with #45.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\ngit commit -F /tmp/claude-1000/-home-leon0399-Projects-llame/a8b08149-66dc-4dc6-94b9-fa9c75f96110/scratchpad/commit-msg-46.txt",
